Description . Pupal cases mostly straight. Greatest length, including anterior antennal processes 10.0–11.0 mm; greatest width of thorax 2.0– 2.1 mm ; greatest width of abdomen 1.5 –2.0 mm, tapering to 1.0– 1.1 mm at greatest width of abdominal segment 8 . Integument subshining light golden brown, becoming darker apically on wing sheaths and to a lesser extent on leg sheaths. Spines and other processes glistening reddish brown; spines uniformly colored or either darker basally or on apical half; processes of head and abdominal segment 9 darker apically (
Fig. 1
).
